<paragraph blockId="2.[173,660,194,1729]" pageId="2" pageNumber="169">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,296,460,481]" pageId="2" pageNumber="169">
<typeStatus box="[197,292,460,481]" pageId="2" pageNumber="169">Paratype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Female. Similar to male except as follows: antennal club as long as preceding 4 segments combined; head and pronotal punctation deeper. Visible abdominal sternites 2–4 nearly convex, with scattered, short setae near midline; sternite 5 with many punctures and long setae; anal plate large, widely convex, with shallow punctures and scattered slender setae. Both apical spurs of metatibia widened, curved, with rounded apices. Ventral genital plates well-sclerotized, nearly symmetrical, widely convex with some apical setae; dorsal genital plates fused at midline, with 3 apical lobes and some short setae on distal borders (
<figureCitation box="[259,319,805,826]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[175,215,901,920]" captionTargetBox="[158,1154,183,895]" captionTargetId="figure-387@1.[151,1171,183,916]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1–7. Phyllophaga aragoni. 1) Head and pronotum; 2) Male protarsal claw; 3) Female genital plates, ventral view; 4) Parameres, distal view; 5) Complete genital capsule, lateral view; 6) Complete genital capsule, dorsal view; 7) Detail of apex of inner sac, distal view. Scale bars = 2 mm, except in Fig. 2 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4893166" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4893166/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="169">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Body length: 
<quantity box="[475,565,805,826]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.08" pageId="2" pageNumber="169" unit="mm" value="20.8">20.8 mm</quantity>
. Humeral width: 
<quantity box="[242,322,832,853]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.8" pageId="2" pageNumber="169" unit="mm" value="8.8">8.8 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
